XML context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="ὅπωσπερ_πλόκον_1179">. The primary meaning of this act was self-dedication (1173 n.), but Teucer here gives it a further significance, suggested by the circumstances of the moment; exactly as in <ref n="Hom. Il. 3.300"> <title>Il.</title> 3. 300</ref> the <quote xml:lang="grc">σπονδαί</quote> at the truce are turned into a symbol of death for those who break the truce,—<quote xml:lang="grc">ὧδέ σφ’ ἐγκέφαλος χαμάδις ῥέοι ὡς ὅδε οἶνος</quote>. Cp. <cit> <bibl n="Liv. 1. 24">Liv. 1. 24</bibl> <quote xml:lang="lat">si prior defexit...tu illo die, Iuppiter, populum Romanum sic ferito ut ego hunc porcum hic hodie feriam.</quote> </cit> <cit> <bibl n="Theoc. 2">Theocr. 2. 28</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc"> <l>ὡς τοῦτον τὸν καρὸν ἐγὼ σὺν δαίμονι τάκω </l> <l>ὣς τάκοιθ’ ὑπ’ ἔρωτος ὁ Μύνδιος αὐτίκα Δέλφις</l> </quote> </cit> . </gloss>

