XML context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="χρυσοῦ_ὑπεροπλίαις_130">, ‘in the haughty pride of clanging gold.’ <quote xml:lang="grc">ὑπεροπλίαις</quote> seems a certain correction of <quote xml:lang="grc">ὑπεροπτίας</quote> (see cr. n.), and has justly won its way with recent edd. The word is fitting, since <quote xml:lang="grc">ὑπεροπλία</quote> is prop. ‘overweening confidence in arms’; and Soph. has used the epic plur. with the epic <quote xml:lang="grc">ι—</quote>, <cit> <bibl n="Hom. Il. 1.205"> <title>Il.</title> 1.205</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ᾗς ὑπεροπλίῃσι</quote> </cit>: so too <cit> <bibl n="Theoc. 25">Theocr. 25. 138</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">σθένεϊ ᾧ | ἠδ’ ὑπεροπλίῃ Φαέθων</quote> </cit> </gloss>

