            citation content, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="στάζει_θυηλῆς_1422">: the gen. depends on the notion of fulness; cp. <ref n="Soph. OC 16"> <title>O. C.</title> 16</ref> <quote xml:lang="grc">βρύων</quote> | <quote xml:lang="grc">δάφνης</quote>: fr. 264 <quote xml:lang="grc">ἀραχνᾶν βρίθει</quote>. (There is no other example of <quote xml:lang="grc">στάζω</quote> in this constr., for in fr. 491, <quote xml:lang="grc">ὀπὸν..στάζοντα τομῆς</quote>, the sense is, ‘sap dripping <emph>from</emph> the cleft wood.’)— The <quote xml:lang="grc">θυηλή</quote> is <quote xml:lang="grc">φόνος</quote>. Cp. <cit> <bibl n="Shak. 1H4 4.1">Shakesp. <title>H. IV.</title>, pt. 1, act 4, sc. 1, 113,</bibl> <quote xml:lang="eng">‘They come like sacrifices in their trim, | And to the fire-eyed maid of smoky war | All hot and bleeding will we offer them.’</quote> </cit> </gloss>

