The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="εἰ_ἔχοι_352">is an abstract statement of the condition: — " <title>Supposing</title> him to have tendance, she is content." For optat. in protasis, with pres. ind. in apodosis, cp. <cit> <bibl>Antiphanes fr. incert. 51 (Bothe p. 412)</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc"> <lg type="trimeter"> <l>εἰ γὰρ ἀφέλοι τις τοῦ βίου τὰς ἡδονάς,</l> <l>καταλείπετ’ οὐδὲν ἕτερον ἢ τεθνηκέναι</l> </lg> </quote> </cit>, " <emph>supposing</emph> one takes away...then nothing is left." </gloss>.

