The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="ἔπους_χάριν_443">, for <emph>lack of</emph> a few words in his defence ( <quote xml:lang="grc">ἀντιλογίας βραχείας</quote> , schol.). As if one said, "They incurred all this loss <emph>for the sake of</emph> a petty sum" ( <foreign xml:lang="lat">i.e.</foreign> to <emph> save</emph> it). This is a slight deviation from the ordinary use of <quote xml:lang="grc">ἕνεκα, οὕνεκα</quote> <ref n="Soph. OC 22">(22)</ref> , <quote xml:lang="grc">ἕκατι, χάριν</quote> , in such phrases. Cp. <cit> <bibl>fr. 510. 6</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc"> <lg type="trimeter"> <l>κἀμοὶ γὰρ ἂν πατήρ γε δακρύων χάριν</l> <l>ἀνῆκτ’ ἂν εἰς φῶς</l> </lg> </quote> </cit>, would have been brought up, <emph>if tears could bring him:</emph> <cit> <bibl n="Aesch. Pers. 337" ref="Aesch. Pers. 337"> Aesch. <title>Pers.</title> 337</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">πλήθους...ἕκατι</quote> </cit>, if numbers could give victory. </gloss>.

