The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="πρόσθε_1549">, before he blinded himself (cp. <ref n="Soph. OT 1183"> <title>O. T.</title> 1183</ref>). The full thought is,— <quote xml:lang="eng"> "Once I <emph>saw</emph> thee, but for long I have only <emph>felt</emph> thee, and now I <emph>feel</emph> thee for the last time."</quote>Whitelaw cp. <cit> <bibl> <title>Par. Lost</title> 3. 21,</bibl> <quote> <lg type="verse" subtype="iambic-pentameter"> <l>Thee I revisit safe,</l> <l> <emph>And</emph>feel <emph>thy sovran vital</emph> lamp; <emph>but thou</emph> </l> <l> <emph>Revisit'st not these eyes.</emph> </l> </lg> </quote> </cit> And <cit> <bibl> <title>Lear</title> 4. 1. 23</bibl> <quote> <lg type="verse" subtype="iambic-pentameter"> <l>Might I but live to see thee in my touch,</l> <l>I'd say I had eyes again.</l> </lg> </quote> </cit> </gloss>.

