The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="πέπων_437">. The metaphor is not directly from the mellowing of fruit, but from the medical use of the word in ref. to the subsiding of inflammation (as in angry tumours, etc.). Cp. the fig. sense of <quote xml:lang="grc">ὠμός</quote> . So <cit> <quote xml:lang="grc">πεπαίνεσθαι</quote> <bibl>Hippocr. 1170 B</bibl> </cit>: <cit> <bibl n="Aristot. Meteo. 4.3" ref="Aristot. Meteo. 4.3"> Arist. <title>Meteor.</title> 4.3</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ἡ φυμάτων <note anchored="true" place="inline" resp="RCJ" xml:lang="eng">(tumours)</note>καὶ φλέγματος...πέπανσις</quote> </cit>: <cit> <bibl> <title>Anthol. Pal.</title> 12. 80</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc"> <lg type="elegiacs"> <l part="F">τί σοι τὸ πεπανθὲν Ἔρωτος</l> <l>τραῦμα διὰ σπλάγχνων αὖθις ἀναφλέγεται;</l> </lg> </quote> </cit>Hence, too, <cit> <bibl n="Soph. Trach. 728" ref="Soph. Trach. 728"> <title>Tr.</title> 728</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ὀργὴ πέπειρα</quote> </cit> . </gloss>.

