The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="σκληρὰ_λέγων_774">, putting hard purposes into soft words: disguising the ungenerous treatment which was really contemplated <ref n="Soph. OC 399">(399)</ref> under the name of a recall to home and friends <ref n="Soph. OC 757"> (757)</ref> . For the verbal contrast cp. <cit> <bibl>Epicharmus fr. 121</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ὦ πονηρέ, μὴ τὰ μαλακὰ μώεο μὴ τὰ σκλήρ’ ἔχῃς</quote> </cit>, "woo not softness, lest thou wed hardness." <cit> <bibl n="Aristot. Rh. 3.7.10" ref="Aristot. Rh. 3.7.10"> Arist. <title>Rhet.</title> 3.7.10</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc"> <note anchored="true" place="inline" resp="RCJ" xml:lang="eng">(speaking of the relation to be observed between the <emph>sounds</emph>sounds<emph> tones</emph>tones</note>ἐὰν οὖν τὰ μαλακὰ σκληρῶς καὶ τὰ σκληρὰ μαλακῶς λέγηται, ἀπίθανον γίγνεται</quote> </cit>. Cp. <ref n="Soph. OC 1406">1406</ref> .</gloss>.

