The xml context, if available, is: <gloss xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="τὸ_καίρια_808">, the reading of Suidas, is supported by such passages as <cit> <bibl n="Aesch. PB 927" ref="Aesch. PB 927"> Aesch. <title>PV</title> 927</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ὅσον τό τ’ ἄρχειν καὶ τὸ δουλεύειν δίχα</quote> </cit>: <cit> <bibl n="Eur. Alc. 528" ref="Eur. Alc. 528"> Eur. <title>Alc.</title> 528</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">χωρὶς τό τ’ εἶναι καὶ τὸ μὴ νομίζεται</quote> </cit>. In <cit> <bibl> Philemon <title xml:lang="grc">Σικελικός</title> fr. 1. 7</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">ἕτερον τό τ’ ἀλγεῖν καὶ τὸ θεωρεῖν ἔστ’ ἴσως</quote> </cit>, the second <quote xml:lang="grc">τὸ</quote> is doubtful. But for <quote xml:lang="grc"> <emph>τὰ</emph> καίρια</quote>, the reading of the MSS., it may be urged that the phrase is <quote xml:lang="grc"> <emph>τὰ</emph> καίρια</quote>( <quote xml:lang="grc">λέγειν, δρᾶν</quote> etc.) in <ref n="Aesch. Seven 1"> Aesch. <title>Th.</title> 1</ref>, <ref n="Aesch. Seven 619">619</ref> , <ref n="Aesch. Supp. 446"> <title>Suppl.</title> 446</ref>, <ref n="Aesch. Lib. 582"> <title>Ch.</title> 582</ref>, <ref n="Eur. IA 829"> Eur. <title>I. A.</title> 829</ref>, <ref n="Soph. Aj. 120"> Soph. <title>Ai.</title> 120</ref>, while <cit> <bibl n="Soph. El. 228" ref="Soph. El. 228"> <title>El.</title> 228</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">φρονοῦντι καίρια</quote> </cit>(without art.) is isolated. If <foreign xml:lang="grc">τὰ</foreign> is retained, the ellipse of <quote xml:lang="grc">τὸ</quote> is illustrated by <ref n="Soph. OC 606">606</ref> , where <ref target="cl606">see n.</ref> : and add <cit> <bibl>trag. incert. fr. 469</bibl> <quote xml:lang="grc">χωρὶς τὰ Μυσῶν καὶ Φρυγῶν ὁρίσματα</quote> </cit>. </gloss>.

